FPbase Data Pipeline
============================================================

=== Step 1: Fetch FPbase data ===
[fetch] GET https://www.fpbase.org/api/proteins/
[fetch] Saved 1040 records → data/fpbase_raw.json
[fetch] GET https://www.fpbase.org/api/proteins/basic/
[fetch] Saved 814 records → data/fpbase_basic_raw.json
Full records   : 1040
Basic records  : 814

=== Step 2: Parse records ===
Records with sequence : 990
Records without seq   : 50
Unique sequences      : 990
After dedup by seq    : 990  (removed 0 duplicates)
Raw FASTA written     : data/fp_sequences_raw.fasta  (990 sequences)

=== Step 3: MAFFT alignment (default settings) ===
Running: mafft --auto --quiet data/fp_sequences_raw.fasta
Aligned sequences     : 990  → data/fp_sequences_aligned.fasta

=== Step 4: trimAl filtering ===
  residue overlap  >= 90%
  sequence overlap >= 90%
Running: trimal -in data/fp_sequences_aligned.fasta -out data/fp_sequences_trimmed.fasta -resoverlap 0.9 -seqoverlap 90
After trimAl          : 986  → data/fp_sequences_trimmed.fasta


=== Step 5: Merge filtered sequences with properties ===
Sequences kept by trimAl: 986
Rows before filter    : 990
Rows after filter     : 986
Cleaned CSV saved     : data/fp_cleaned.csv

Property coverage in cleaned dataset:
  ex_max         : 872/986 (88.4%)
  em_max         : 833/986 (84.5%)
  ext_coeff      : 623/986 (63.2%)
  qy             : 693/986 (70.3%)
  brightness     : 599/986 (60.8%)
  pka            : 402/986 (40.8%)
  maturation     : 177/986 (18.0%)
  lifetime       : 191/986 (19.4%)
  bleach         : 188/986 (19.1%)
  agg            : 668/986 (67.7%)
  cofactor       : 59/986 (6.0%)

=== Pipeline complete ===
Final dataset: 986 FP sequences with properties
Output: data/fp_cleaned.csv
